<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>à la guerre comme à la guerre • c’est la guerre</xh5><p> <i>à la guerre comme à la guerre</i>—(Fr.) is used to tell a person to make do with what one has or do what one has to do: She walked ... with a certain rebellion burning in her heart. It was not the right sort of heart to take to a love-meeting. But <u>à la guerre comme à la guerre</u>!</p><p> <i>c’est la guerre</i>—(Fr.) an ironic phrase to provide an excuse for anything that has not gone quite to plan: The long string of projects which were started were never brought to commercial viability But, <u>c’est la guerre</u>, eh?</p> </entry>
